## ğŸ§° Template 2: Using AI to Rewrite for Audience Clarity

**Use When:** A technical update needs to be made user-friendly.

```
You are using AI to simplify or reframe dense info for a broader audience.

Friction â†’ Engineering docs or legal copy is hard for teams to digest.  
Bridge â†’ AI can help rephrase, but needs accurate grounding.  
Evidence â†’ Without prompt clarity, AI may oversimplify or hallucinate.  
Implication â†’ Misinformed simplification leads to bad decisions.  
Action â†’ Use layered prompting. First: Simplify without dumbing down. Then: Validate facts.  
Look Ahead â†’ Add a human sign-off step before distribution.
```

---

### âœ… Example 2

```
You are rewriting a data policy update for all employees.

Friction â†’ Original copy is 900 words of legal and security terms.  
Bridge â†’ AI is used to identify structure, not to invent meaning.  
Evidence â†’ It helped chunk content into â€œWhat changed / Why / Impactâ€ format.  
Implication â†’ But one section introduced inaccurate wording around user consent.  
Action â†’ Manually rewrote that part and included proper legal review.  
Look Ahead â†’ Feedback survey will test understanding of this change.
```

